                            "termAccession": ""
                        },
                        "description": "<p>First, Enterococcus faecalis (E. faecalis MM1) and Lactobacillus reuteri  (L. reuteri ATCC 6475) were grown in basal defined medium containing 250 mM glycerol for 24 h at 37 \u00b0C. The supernatant fluids of each culture were then filter-sterilized and stored for subsequent LC-MS analysis or mixed at equal volume with basal defined media.</p><p><br></p><p>Second, E. faecalis MM1 was grown on basal defined medium mixed with equal volumes of the spent medium of L. reuteri ATCC 6475 (0.2 mL total volume distributed in 96-well plates). Similarly, L. reuteri ATCC 6475 was grown for 24 h at 37\u2009\u00b0C on basal defined medium mixed with equal volumes of the spent medium of E. faecalis MM1.The supernatant fluids of each of these cultures were filter-sterilized for subsequent LC-MS analysis.</p>",
                        "uri": "",
                        "version": "",
                        "parameters": [
                            {
                                "comments": [],
                                "parameterName": {
                                    "comments": [],
                                    "annotationValue": "",
                                    "termSource": null,
