                        "name": "Extraction",
                        "protocolType": {
                            "comments": [],
                            "annotationValue": "Extraction",
                            "termSource": null,
                            "termAccession": ""
                        },
                        "description": "<p>For metabolite extraction, a volume of 100 \u03bcL from each supernatant fraction was mixed with 1 mL of pre-cooled metabolomics extraction mixture (methanol containing 2.5 \u03bcg/mL ampicillin). Tubes were incubated for 10 min in an orbital shaker, prior to their centrifugation at full speed for 10 min. For polar metabolite analysis, 150 \u03bcL of extracted metabolites were transferred to glass vials and kept at -20\u2009\u00b0C until used. QC's were prepared by mixing equal volumes of all samples and then processed as for the samples.</p>",
                        "uri": "",
                        "version": "",
                        "parameters": [
