                            "annotationValue": "Chromatography",
                            "termSource": null,
                            "termAccession": ""
                        },
                        "description": "<p>A volume of 5 \u03bcL of each sample was injected into a ACQUITY UPLC BEH C18 100 mm x 2.1 mm, 1.7 \u03bcm reversed phase column (Waters, Milford, MA, US) using a Waters Acquity UPLC system. Mobile phases consisted of 0.1% formic acid (A) and acetonitrile, supplemented with 0.1% formic acid (B) (UPLC MS grade, BioSolve). The metabolites were eluted at a flow rate of 400 \u03bcL/min, using the following percentages of (A): 1.0 min gradient from 99 to 95%; 7.0 min gradient from 95 to 1%; 2.9 min at 1%; 0.1 min gradient from 1 to 5%; 2.0 min gradient from 5 to 99% and 2 min at 99% for washing and re-equilibrated of the column (15 min total run time).</p>",
