                            "termSource": null,
                            "termAccession": ""
                        },
                        "description": "<p>The mass spectra were acquired using an Exactive mass spectrometer (Thermo-Fisher, Bremen, Germany). The spectra were recorded using both full scan and all-ion fragmentation scan mode, covering a mass range of 100-1500 m/z. The resolution was set to 70,000 with 10 scans/s, restricting the Orbitrap loading time to a maximum of 100 ms with a target value of 1e^5 ions. The capillary voltage was set to 3.5 kV with a sheath gas flow value of 60 and an auxiliary gas flow of 20. The capillary temperature was set at 275 \u00b0C, while the drying gas in the heated electrospray source was set at 300 \u00b0C.</p>",
