                            "termSource": null,
                            "termAccession": ""
                        },
                        "description": "<p>Chromatogram processing, peak detection and integration was performed using <strong>MZmine 2</strong> (v2.41.2)<strong>[1]</strong> with signal to noise ratio&nbsp;set to 5. Production metabolites were defined when the ratio of [metabolites after growth/metabolites before growth] was equal or superior to 2.5.&nbsp;Consumption of metabolites was defined when the same ratio was equal or inferior to 0.4. To increase stringency, production or consumption of a metabolite was further confirmed if the metabolite was produced or consumed in 3 biological replicates. Metabolites that were neither produced or consumed by E. faecalis or L.reuteri were ignored. </p><p><br></p><p><strong>Ref:</strong></p><p><strong>[1]</strong> Pluskal T, Castillo S, Villar-Briones A, Oresic M. MZmine 2: modular framework for processing, visualizing, and analyzing mass spectrometry-based molecular profile data. BMC Bioinformatics. 2010 Jul 23;11:395. doi:10.1186/1471-2105-11-395. PMID:20650010.</p>",
                        "uri": "",
                        "version": "",
                        "parameters": [
